# Spells

Magic in Autumn Phoenix RPG adapts to the caster. The same spell produces different effects depending on whether you cast it through intellect, instinct, determination, or force of personality. This flexibility means every spellcaster develops their own unique style.

## Casting Spells

Every spell requires a casting roll: **2d6 + [Chosen Attribute] + Sorcery**

You choose which attribute to use each time you cast. This decision determines both your chance of success and the spell's specific effects.

### The Four Magical Traditions

**Mind + Sorcery - Calculated Precision**
You weave magic through pure intellect, achieving surgical control. Your spells avoid allies, maximize efficiency, and demonstrate technical mastery.

**Awareness + Sorcery - Instinctive Power**
You channel magic through intuition and perception, sensing weaknesses and vulnerabilities. Your spells hit harder and exploit what others miss.

**Will + Sorcery - Unyielding Determination**
You impose your will on reality through sheer force of determination. You can cast even at negative Momentum, and your magic persists through resistance.

**Presence + Sorcery - Commanding Reality**
You reshape the world through personality and conviction. Your magic affects minds and emotions, creating effects that transcend mere physics.

Most spellcasters favor one approach but use all four when circumstances demand it.

