## Building Your Spell Repertoire

Different spellcasters will build different repertoires based on their attributes, calling, and party role. These are proven starting points, not rigid requirements.

### Essential Cantrips

**Spark** - Combat Momentum generation. Cast this in Aggressive stance to build Momentum rapidly.

**Mage Armor** - Survivability foundation. Most spellcasters want this active.

**Light** - Utility staple. Solves common problems without costing resources.

**Prestidigitation** - Versatility tool. Creative uses emerge during play.

### Core Spell Toolkit

**Bolt** - Reliable ranged damage at 0 Momentum cost. Your bread-and-butter attack.

**Shield** - Emergency protection. Saves lives when you need it.

**Blur** - Sustained defense for dangerous situations.

**Charm** - Social conflicts become winnable with this.

### Power Options

**Fireball** - Area damage when you need to hit multiple targets.

**Heal** - Party support that keeps allies fighting.

**Fly** - Tactical mobility that changes how fights work.

**Invisibility** - Infiltration and escape rolled into one.

### Specialized Choices

Choose advanced and master spells based on:
- Campaign needs (urban vs wilderness vs dungeon)
- Party composition (what gaps need filling)
- Your preferred magical tradition (Mind/Awareness/Will/Presence)
- Momentum economy planning (can you afford expensive spells)

